caption: We now have a right to know where we'll be welcomed and where we'll be treated like lepers; this is a legitimate criticism. I regularly ordered from this location for pick-up, which takes seconds if it's prepaid and ready. On 3/9/21 my food had been paid for and was overdue for pickup. I walked in without a mask to be instantly "greeted" with hostility by a phalanx of about five employees who all freaked out in unison. I said my food was ready and I'd grab it and be gone. Nope, not good enough. They insisted I put one on just for the hand-off. I refused this nonsense and demanded my food, which was so close I could almost reach it myself. The male nurse in charge told me to lose the attitude and I told him his attitude was going to lose a customer. And guess what? He was totally groovy with that. Along with safety measures, struggling restaurants should also start using common sense and stop pretending to be epidemiologists. Hourly earners must respect the customers whose patronage pays their wages and businesses that expect patrons to remain obedient to their hysterical and inflexible demands should also expect to see fewer customers, and more reviews like this. I will not be returning nor do I need re-education, so a pro-forma response-lecture citing "Science, CDC & City of Boise" yada-yada is not required.

Today was my sons bday, and me, my sister, son and nephew decided to celebrate by eating at BWW.  It turned out to be a horrible experience and if it hadn't been his bday, we would have gotten up and left.  First, our server brought us some menus and we ordered food and one of the drink specials.  She came back about 5 minutes later and said she couldn't honor the drink prices on the menu she gave us because it was an old menu.  We were confused, but fine with it because obviously she had made a mistake.  Then they bring our fries out without the other food we had ordered.  I asked them to bring all our food out together because nobody wants their entree's separately.  It's like ordering a sandwich and they just bring you the bread and tell you to eat it while you're waiting for the meet/cheese, it doesn't make sense.  She said she could bring them out with the rest of our food, but that they would be cold.  I asked to speak to the manager, but she never showed up.  After awhile, I got up and and asked the front desk person for the manager and waited there in the front until she came out to talk to me.  She honored the drink price that we were given, but told us we could only have 1 drink. When they finally did bring us our our food, they didn't bring out my sister's order.  About 10 minutes went by, and I had to get up and go find our server to ask where it was.  When they finally did bring it, our server said that the cooks had messed up our order in the back and forgot to make her food.  So we all had to sit there and let our food get cold until she had hers too.  Our service was unacceptable for the amount of money I spent, and we will not be eating there ever again.

I am a big fan of Wing stop and decided to try Buffalo Wild Wings for a change. I visited their Website on 3rd April 2020 and saw there is free delivery due to lock down. I ordered 30 wings (4 flavors) , 2 veggie sticks and one large fries. I opted sauce on side as I was not familiar with the taste. Total came around $43.xx. Food was delivered on time by some third party company. I opened the food 30 min later and found there was no sauce provided with the food. It was just 30 plain fired Wings. I called the store immediately and got hold of them after 30 min. person took the phone asked me to call the delivery company initially. When i told i have nothing to do with them, she promised to refund the money and told her manager will call me next day morning. But never received any call. so i called the next day and another guy took my phone number, name and last four digit of my credit card and said I will get refund, but never happened. I called 3rd time and also had same experience. I decided to let the money go. I never had such a bad experience from any restaurant in my life. I waited 2 weeks before posting this to make sure they have no intention to refund the money and apologize for the inconvenience caused. Tom
